						               													<description>Subtitled, &amp;quot;Fighting sea battles with model ships,&amp;quot; this is a hardbound book containing many aspects of gaming naval warfare with miniatures.  It also includes some other board games one can make with the directions in the book.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Contents include:&amp;#10;Section One: Games Using Model Ships&amp;#10;  Naval War Games as Tactical Training&amp;#10;  Map Games&amp;#10;  'Battleships'&amp;#10;  Commercial Games&amp;#10;  Table-top Islands&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Section Two: Model Ships for War Games&amp;#10;  Sources of Supply&amp;#10;  Home Construction of Model Ships&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Section Three: Rules for Fighting Naval War Games&amp;#10;  Ancient Period&amp;#10;  Spanish Armada&amp;#10;  Mid-Eighteenth Century&amp;#10;  Napoleonic Period&amp;#10;  American Civil War&amp;#10;  Late Nineteenth Century&amp;#10;  Early Twentieth Century&amp;#10;  World Wars I and II - Charles Dick's Rules&amp;#10;  Hunt the Raider&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Section Four: The Pioneers of Naval War-Gaming&amp;#10;  The Rules of Fred Jane - Early Twentieth Century&amp;#10;  The Fletcher Pratt Naval War Game - Modern&amp;#10;  Additional Factors and Rules&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Section Five: Operational Choices&amp;#10;  The Best Sea Wars to Fight&amp;#10;  Combined Operations&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Section Six: Research&amp;#10;  Books&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The book has many different rules sets for naval warfare, as you can see from the above.  It's also fairly well illustrated, both with photos and drawings.  A very detailed and well-written book, recommended if you have any interest in naval miniatures gaming.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Microbadge:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
